GSE145926 bronchoalveolar lavage single cell transcriptome COVID19 (Seurat analysis)¶

GSE145926 dataset evaluate Single-cell landscape of bronchoalveolar immune cells in COVID-19 patients. It comprised 12 experiments: 6 were performed on Healthy donor samples, 3 on mild COVID19 patients and 3 on severe COVID19 patients. This dataset is accessible at the folowing address: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE145926 After downloading GSE145926.sh BASH script at following address: https://github.com/cdesterke/covid19sc in linux terminal (BASH) you can execute it to download the entire dataset with the command: ./GSE145926.sh it will create a folder nammed GSE145925 comprising the 12 experiments in h5 format.

## Build a merged Seurat object with the 12 experiments
all <- merge(control_51, y = c(control_52, control_100, control_148, control_149, control_152 , mildcovid_141, mildcovid_142, mildcovid_144, severecovid_143, severecovid_145, severecovid_146 ), add.cell.ids = c("ct51", "ct52","ct100","ct148","ct149","ct152","mc141", "mc142", "mc144", "sc143","sc145","sc146"), project = "covid")

## description of the object with cell origins and normalization
list <- SplitObject(all, split.by = "orig.ident")
list <- lapply(X = list, FUN = function(x) {
x <- NormalizeData(x)
x <- FindVariableFeatures(x, selection.method = "vst", nfeatures = 2000)
})
